<glossary>
<definition id="def-00001"><term>amylase</term> <meaning>an enzyme in the saliva and pancreatic juice that catalyzes the breaking down of starch, glycogen, and related polysaccharides into more simple and readily usable forms of sugar</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00002"><term>lipase</term> <meaning>pancreatic enzyme that breaks down triglycerides into free fatty acids and glycerol to be used in the body</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00003"><term>protease</term> <meaning>pancreatic enzyme that breaks down proteins in the diet; also provides protection from organisms that may live in the intestines, such as certain bacteria and yeast</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
